  "name": "The Story Tree: Children's Stories for Every Age",
  "description": "A curated collection of 33 essential children's stories drawn from the world's great traditions — Aesop's fables, Grimm and Andersen fairy tales, Greek and Norse myths, folk tales from six continents, and beloved classics of children's literature. Each story is told four ways: a gentle preschool version for the youngest listeners, a faithful classic telling, cultural roots showing how the story travels across traditions, and a modern reflection on why it still matters. Cross-linked to full source grammars in this repository.\n\nPUBLIC DOMAIN ILLUSTRATION REFERENCES: Arthur Rackham's fairy tale illustrations (1900s-1920s) — atmospheric watercolors for Grimm, Andersen, and Aesop. Walter Crane's picture books (1870s-1890s) — Art Nouveau nursery illustrations. Edmund Dulac's fairy tale plates (1907-1916) — rich color illustrations for Arabian Nights, Andersen, and myth collections. Gustave Doré's fairy tale engravings (1862-1870s) — dramatic black-and-white for Perrault and La Fontaine. John Tenniel's Alice illustrations (1865) — the definitive Alice in Wonderland images. W.W. Denslow's Oz illustrations (1900) — original Wizard of Oz art. Randolph Caldecott's nursery illustrations (1878-1886) — lively watercolors of folk tales and nursery rhymes.",
  "grammar_type": "custom",
  "creator_name": "PlayfulProcess",
  "creator_link": "https://lifeisprocess.substack.com/",
